<h2 id="set-up-adjustment-codes-for-ipi-taxes" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="105">Set up adjustment codes for IPI taxes</h2>
<ol sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="107">
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="107">On the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="107">IPI adjustment codes table</strong> page, enter an adjustment code. The first character must be <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="107">0</strong> (zero) for a credit adjustment or <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="107">1</strong> for a debit adjustment.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="108">Enter a description.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="109">If the adjustment code will be used to report the reversal of an Imposto sobre Produtos Industrializados (IPI) tax amount that was previously reported, select the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/latam-bra-configure-fiscal-books.md" sourcestartlinenumber="109">Reversal adjustment code</strong> option.</li>
